      "text": "*magenta-scripts.txt*        Authoring Magenta Scripts          *magenta-scripts*\n\n                          MAGENTA.NVIM SCRIPTS\n                     Automations that drive agent threads\n\n==============================================================================\nCONTENTS                                            *magenta-scripts-contents*\n\n    1. Introduction .......................... |magenta-scripts-introduction|\n    2. Where Scripts Live .................... |magenta-scripts-locations|\n    3. Discovery (index.ts) .................. |magenta-scripts-discovery|\n    4. Importing the SDK ..................... |magenta-scripts-sdk|\n    5. registerScript Contract ............... |magenta-scripts-register|\n    6. The Runner ............................ |magenta-scripts-runner|\n    7. Example ............................... |magenta-scripts-example|\n    8. Testing ............................... |magenta-scripts-testing|\n\n==============================================================================\nINTRODUCTION                                   *magenta-scripts-introduction*\n\nScripts are TypeScript automations that run as a child process of the magenta\nnode process. Unlike skills (|magenta-skills|), which inject knowledge into\nthe system prompt, a script is code that orchestrates one or more real,\nsidebar-visible agent threads and reports progress back to magenta.\n\nScripts are triggered by the agent via the script-running tool, or run\noutside the lifecycle of a single thread. They report progress in the\n\"Scripts\" section of the magenta overview.\n\n==============================================================================\nWHERE SCRIPTS LIVE                                *magenta-scripts-locations*\n\nEach script package lives in its own subdirectory of the project's\n\\`.magenta/scripts/\\` directory, so multiple independent installations can\ncoexist:\n\n\u003e\n  .magenta/scripts/\n  └── my-package/\n      ├── magenta-sdk/      # SDK shim maintained by magenta\n      ├── index.ts          # entry point (required)\n      ├── code-review.ts    # a script module\n      └── implement-plan.ts # another script module\n\u003c\n\n==============================================================================\nDISCOVERY                                         *magenta-scripts-discovery*\n\nMagenta discovers scripts by forking each package's \\`index.ts\\` file — that is\nthe only file it ever executes per package. \\`index.ts\\` must import every\nscript module so their top-level \\`registerScript()\\` calls run:\n\n\u003etypescript\n  // .magenta/scripts/my-package/index.ts\n  import \"./code-review.ts\";\n  import \"./implement-plan.ts\";\n\u003c",
      "contextualizedText": "*magenta-scripts.txt*        Authoring Magenta Scripts          *magenta-scripts*\n\n                          MAGENTA.NVIM SCRIPTS\n                     Automations that drive agent threads\n\n==============================================================================\nCONTENTS                                            *magenta-scripts-contents*\n\n    1. Introduction .......................... |magenta-scripts-introduction|\n    2. Where Scripts Live .................... |magenta-scripts-locations|\n    3. Discovery (index.ts) .................. |magenta-scripts-discovery|\n    4. Importing the SDK ..................... |magenta-scripts-sdk|\n    5. registerScript Contract ............... |magenta-scripts-register|\n    6. The Runner ............................ |magenta-scripts-runner|\n    7. Example ............................... |magenta-scripts-example|\n    8. Testing ............................... |magenta-scripts-testing|\n\n==============================================================================\nINTRODUCTION                                   *magenta-scripts-introduction*\n\nScripts are TypeScript automations that run as a child process of the magenta\nnode process. Unlike skills (|magenta-skills|), which inject knowledge into\nthe system prompt, a script is code that orchestrates one or more real,\nsidebar-visible agent threads and reports progress back to magenta.\n\nScripts are triggered by the agent via the script-running tool, or run\noutside the lifecycle of a single thread. They report progress in the\n\"Scripts\" section of the magenta overview.\n\n==============================================================================\nWHERE SCRIPTS LIVE                                *magenta-scripts-locations*\n\nEach script package lives in its own subdirectory of the project's\n\\`.magenta/scripts/\\` directory, so multiple independent installations can\ncoexist:\n\n\u003e\n  .magenta/scripts/\n  └── my-package/\n      ├── magenta-sdk/      # SDK shim maintained by magenta\n      ├── index.ts          # entry point (required)\n      ├── code-review.ts    # a script module\n      └── implement-plan.ts # another script module\n\u003c\n\n==============================================================================\nDISCOVERY                                         *magenta-scripts-discovery*\n\nMagenta discovers scripts by forking each package's \\`index.ts\\` file — that is\nthe only file it ever executes per package. \\`index.ts\\` must import every\nscript module so their top-level \\`registerScript()\\` calls run:\n\n\u003etypescript\n  // .magenta/scripts/my-package/index.ts\n  import \"./code-review.ts\";\n  import \"./implement-plan.ts\";\n\u003c",
      "headingContext": "",
      "startLine": 0,
      "startCol": 0,
      "endLine": 0,
      "endCol": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "Any other \\`.ts\\` files (script modules, shared libraries) are never forked\ndirectly; they only run because \\`index.ts\\` (or another module) imports them.\nThis keeps discovery and thread creation predictable.\n\n==============================================================================\nIMPORTING THE SDK                                       *magenta-scripts-sdk*\n\nImport the SDK through the stable shim that magenta maintains inside each\npackage directory via \\`./magenta-sdk\\`:\n\n\u003etypescript\n  import { registerScript } from \"./magenta-sdk/index.ts\";\n\u003c\n\nDo not import from any other path — the shim resolves to the installed\nplugin's SDK regardless of where the plugin lives on disk.\n\n==============================================================================\nREGISTERSCRIPT CONTRACT                            *magenta-scripts-register*\n\n\u003etypescript\n  registerScript(name, description, parameterSchema, runner);\n\u003c\n\n  name             Unique script name (how agents invoke it).\n  description      Shown to agents so they know when to use it.\n  parameterSchema  A JSON Schema describing the \\`parameters\\` the runner\n                   receives.\n  runner           An async function that does the work\n                   (see |magenta-scripts-runner|).\n\n==============================================================================\nTHE RUNNER                                           *magenta-scripts-runner*\n\nThe runner has the signature \\`runner(parameters, thread, log)\\`:\n\n  parameters       The validated input object.\n\n  thread(prompt, yieldSchema, options?)\n                   Spawns a real magenta thread seeded with \\`prompt\\`,\n                   equipped with a \\`yield_to_parent\\` tool whose input schema\n                   is \\`yieldSchema\\`. Resolves to the structured value the\n                   agent yields. Use the generic to type the result:\n                   \\`await thread\u003c{ done: boolean }\u003e(...)\\`.\n\n                   \\`options\\` may include:\n                     contextFiles     Absolute paths to seed into the\n                                      thread's context.\n                     systemReminder   A recurring system reminder injected\n                                      into the thread.\n                     cwd, profile, model, tools\n\n  log(message)     Reports progress; surfaced in the magenta Scripts section.\n\n==============================================================================\nEXAMPLE                                             *magenta-scripts-example*\n\n\u003etypescript\n  import { registerScript } from \"./magenta-sdk/index.ts\";",
      "contextualizedText": "Any other \\`.ts\\` files (script modules, shared libraries) are never forked\ndirectly; they only run because \\`index.ts\\` (or another module) imports them.\nThis keeps discovery and thread creation predictable.\n\n==============================================================================\nIMPORTING THE SDK                                       *magenta-scripts-sdk*\n\nImport the SDK through the stable shim that magenta maintains inside each\npackage directory via \\`./magenta-sdk\\`:\n\n\u003etypescript\n  import { registerScript } from \"./magenta-sdk/index.ts\";\n\u003c\n\nDo not import from any other path — the shim resolves to the installed\nplugin's SDK regardless of where the plugin lives on disk.\n\n==============================================================================\nREGISTERSCRIPT CONTRACT                            *magenta-scripts-register*\n\n\u003etypescript\n  registerScript(name, description, parameterSchema, runner);\n\u003c\n\n  name             Unique script name (how agents invoke it).\n  description      Shown to agents so they know when to use it.\n  parameterSchema  A JSON Schema describing the \\`parameters\\` the runner\n                   receives.\n  runner           An async function that does the work\n                   (see |magenta-scripts-runner|).\n\n==============================================================================\nTHE RUNNER                                           *magenta-scripts-runner*\n\nThe runner has the signature \\`runner(parameters, thread, log)\\`:\n\n  parameters       The validated input object.\n\n  thread(prompt, yieldSchema, options?)\n                   Spawns a real magenta thread seeded with \\`prompt\\`,\n                   equipped with a \\`yield_to_parent\\` tool whose input schema\n                   is \\`yieldSchema\\`. Resolves to the structured value the\n                   agent yields. Use the generic to type the result:\n                   \\`await thread\u003c{ done: boolean }\u003e(...)\\`.\n\n                   \\`options\\` may include:\n                     contextFiles     Absolute paths to seed into the\n                                      thread's context.\n                     systemReminder   A recurring system reminder injected\n                                      into the thread.\n                     cwd, profile, model, tools\n\n  log(message)     Reports progress; surfaced in the magenta Scripts section.\n\n==============================================================================\nEXAMPLE                                             *magenta-scripts-example*\n\n\u003etypescript\n  import { registerScript } from \"./magenta-sdk/index.ts\";",
      "headingContext": "",
      "startLine": 0,
      "startCol": 0,
      "endLine": 0,
      "endCol": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "registerScript(\n    \"summarize-file\",\n    \"Summarizes a file and returns a one-line summary\",\n    {\n      type: \"object\",\n      properties: { path: { type: \"string\" } },\n      required: [\"path\"],\n    },\n    async (params: { path: string }, thread, log) =\u003e {\n      log(\\`summarizing \\${params.path}\\`);\n      const result = await thread\u003c{ summary: string }\u003e(\n        \\`Read \\${params.path} and summarize it in one sentence.\\`,\n        {\n          type: \"object\",\n          properties: { summary: { type: \"string\" } },\n          required: [\"summary\"],\n        },\n      );\n      log(\\`summary: \\${result.summary}\\`);\n    },\n  );\n\u003c\n\n==============================================================================\nTESTING                                             *magenta-scripts-testing*\n\nUse the in-process test harness from \\`./magenta-sdk/testing.ts\\`. It drives\nthe runner with test-double \\`thread\\`/\\`log\\` — no subprocess and no magenta\nrequired. Statically import the script module first so its \\`registerScript\\`\ncall runs.\n\n\u003etypescript\n  import { expect, it } from \"vitest\";\n  import { runScript } from \"./magenta-sdk/testing.ts\";\n  import \"./summarize-file.ts\"; // registers the script\n\n  it(\"summarizes\", async () =\u003e {\n    const { handle, donePromise } = runScript(\"summarize-file\", {\n      path: \"README.md\",\n    });\n\n    const call = await handle.nextThread();\n    expect(call.prompt).toContain(\"README.md\");\n    call.yield({ summary: \"It is a readme.\" });\n\n    await donePromise;\n    expect(handle.logs).toContain(\"summary: It is a readme.\");\n  });\n\u003c\n\n\\`handle.nextThread()\\` resolves with each pending \\`thread()\\` call (in order),\nexposing \\`prompt\\`, \\`yieldSchema\\`, \\`options\\`, and \\`yield(value)\\` /\n\\`reject(error)\\` to settle that specific call. \\`handle.logs\\` captures \\`log()\\`\noutput.\n\nvim:tw=78:ts=8:noet:ft=help:norl:",
      "contextualizedText": "registerScript(\n    \"summarize-file\",\n    \"Summarizes a file and returns a one-line summary\",\n    {\n      type: \"object\",\n      properties: { path: { type: \"string\" } },\n      required: [\"path\"],\n    },\n    async (params: { path: string }, thread, log) =\u003e {\n      log(\\`summarizing \\${params.path}\\`);\n      const result = await thread\u003c{ summary: string }\u003e(\n        \\`Read \\${params.path} and summarize it in one sentence.\\`,\n        {\n          type: \"object\",\n          properties: { summary: { type: \"string\" } },\n          required: [\"summary\"],\n        },\n      );\n      log(\\`summary: \\${result.summary}\\`);\n    },\n  );\n\u003c\n\n==============================================================================\nTESTING                                             *magenta-scripts-testing*\n\nUse the in-process test harness from \\`./magenta-sdk/testing.ts\\`. It drives\nthe runner with test-double \\`thread\\`/\\`log\\` — no subprocess and no magenta\nrequired. Statically import the script module first so its \\`registerScript\\`\ncall runs.\n\n\u003etypescript\n  import { expect, it } from \"vitest\";\n  import { runScript } from \"./magenta-sdk/testing.ts\";\n  import \"./summarize-file.ts\"; // registers the script\n\n  it(\"summarizes\", async () =\u003e {\n    const { handle, donePromise } = runScript(\"summarize-file\", {\n      path: \"README.md\",\n    });\n\n    const call = await handle.nextThread();\n    expect(call.prompt).toContain(\"README.md\");\n    call.yield({ summary: \"It is a readme.\" });\n\n    await donePromise;\n    expect(handle.logs).toContain(\"summary: It is a readme.\");\n  });\n\u003c\n\n\\`handle.nextThread()\\` resolves with each pending \\`thread()\\` call (in order),\nexposing \\`prompt\\`, \\`yieldSchema\\`, \\`options\\`, and \\`yield(value)\\` /\n\\`reject(error)\\` to settle that specific call. \\`handle.logs\\` captures \\`log()\\`\noutput.\n\n